FBIS4-23673 "drafr114_e_94010" FBIS-AFR-94-114 Daily Report 10 Jun 1994 WEST AFRICA Nigeria Information Minister Denies Reports of Chad Invasion Information Minister Denies Reports of Chad Invasion AB1006220594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network in English 1500 GMT 10 Jun 94 AB1006220594 Lagos Radio Nigeria Network English BFN [Text] Nigerians residing in border areas of the country have again been assured of their safety. The director of defense information, Brigadier General Fred Chijuka, gave the assurance today in an interview with a Radio Nigeria correspondent. On alleged invasion of parts of Borno State by the Chadian Army, the director said that the report was not true. He explained that what happened was that Chadian forces clashed with Chadian rebels near the border with Nigeria. Brig.-Gen. Chijuka asked people living in the border areas not to panic, as the government would ensure adequate protection for them at all times.
